      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="memorial"></a>Sanderstead Memorial Hall</h3>
      <p>You may be aware of Sanderstead Memorial Hall on Purley Oaks Road. It was built as a tribute to the men and women who died or served their country in the First World War. The hall was opened in June 1922 by Vice Admiral A.F.B. Carpenter VC of Zeebrugge fame. The Sanderstead Hall Association was formed in 1923 to manage the hall. The hall is used as a facility for residents of Sanderstead and, subject to availability and proposed use, may be hired. It is used on a regular basis for various activities by several groups. These include: The Cavat School of Dance, Castle Day Nursery, Dog Training Class, Beeches Badminton Club, Sanderstead Hall Badminton Club.</p>
